The paper deals with the construction of spanning trees in metric spaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concepts of unweighted diameter and weight are related to data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.DM), respectively. The use of Euclidean Spanners suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper discusses tight lower bounds, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GR).
